%F A387471 a(n) = d(2*n-1).
%F A387471 Conjecture: a(n) = 6*n - 5 if n mod 5 != 0, and a(n) = 6*n+7 if n mod 5 = 0.
%F A387471 Conjectured g.f.: 6*x/(1-x)^2 - 5*x/(1-x) + 12*x^5/(1-x^5).
%e A387471 n = 1 (m = 1): the three medians concur at one interior point, so a(1) = 1.
%e A387471 n = 2 (m = 3): with 3 cevians per vertex there are 7 interior triple intersections, so a(2) = 7.
%e A387471 n = 3 (m = 5): with 5 cevians per vertex there are 13 interior triple intersections, so a(3) = 13.
